  "description": "Behavioral Adoption Insight Added to TODO.md: Discovered agent used sed for 49 struct modifications instead of Julie's fuzzy_replace despite it being documented. Root cause: Instructions describe WHAT/HOW but not WHEN/WHY to use tools over alternatives. Three knowledge types needed: (1) Declarative (tool exists), (2) Procedural (syntax), (3) Situational (when to choose). Recent token optimization may have stripped too much behavioral guidance. Solution: Add \"When to Use\" sections, behavioral triggers, anti-patterns. Balance token efficiency with adoption effectiveness. This is a real-world example of the behavioral adoption challenge - having the better tool doesn't matter if agents don't know when to reach for it.",
